Sentencas: Achieving high performance from a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) requires optimal design based on parametric analysis.
Titulo: Analysis of Design Parameters in Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using Response Surface Methodology

Sentencas: In this paper, design parameters, including anode support porosity, thicknesses of electrolyte, anode support, and cathode functional layers of a single, intermediate temperature, anode-supported planar SOFC, are analyzed.
Titulo: Analysis of Design Parameters in Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using Response Surface Methodology

Sentencas: The response surface methodology (RSM) technique based on an artificial neural network (ANN) model is used.
Titulo: Analysis of Design Parameters in Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using Response Surface Methodology

Sentencas: The effects of the cell parameters on its performance are calculated to determine the significant design factors and interaction effects.
Titulo: Analysis of Design Parameters in Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using Response Surface Methodology

Sentencas: The obtained optimum parameters are adopted to manufacture the single units of an SOFC through tape casting and screen-printing processes.
Titulo: Analysis of Design Parameters in Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using Response Surface Methodology

Sentencas: The cell is tested and its electrochemical characteristics, which show a satisfactory performance, are discussed.
Titulo: Analysis of Design Parameters in Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using Response Surface Methodology

Sentencas: The measured maximum power density (MPD) of the fabricated SOFC displays a promising performance of 1.39Wcm(-2).
Titulo: Analysis of Design Parameters in Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using Response Surface Methodology

Sentencas: The manufacturing process planned to fabricate the SOFC can be used for industrial production purposes.
